Interface Directory<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of elements in this directory.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DirectoryIFD, PngDirectory, XmpDirectory

    public interface Directory<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Represents a generic collection or directory of entries of a specific type. A Directory provides basic operations for adding, checking for presence, and querying the size and emptiness of the collection. It also extends Iterable, allowing it to be used in enhanced for-loops.
    Since:
    13 October 2025
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Trevor Maggs
